      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PENNY BLACK NZ (5) has returned in terrific form having won her two Gloucester Park starts since a spell, the latest at Group 3 level when she overcame a wider draw. Goes very well here, winning four of five attempts and she'll be race fit third up. The one to beat. ALTA ALLURE (1) came from wider when only 1.2m behind Penny Black last start. That continued her good form and she also drew deeper when winning a G3 in the city last month. Should get every chance from the ace draw. MADAM PUBLISHER NZ (8) draws wide but could be close to a win having placed in her last two outings and has a decent record at this circuit. LITTLE DARLING (9) draws wide again after racing deep and working last start but strikes at 50 per cent at this distance so can feature with better luck. WONDERFUL TO FLY (4) draws lower than when midfield to Penny Black last start. Include.",
